1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:05,380
[brazen music playing]

2
00:00:10,969 --> 00:00:14,222
[upbeat tense music]

3
00:00:16,599 --> 00:00:18,184
- [electronic bleeping]
- [Atoy on radio] <i>Our main target</i>

4
00:00:18,268 --> 00:00:19,352
<i>is Abel Merelli.</i>

5
00:00:19,436 --> 00:00:21,813
<i>Target is in a tinted SUV.</i>

6
00:00:21,896 --> 00:00:22,814
<i>The package rides red.</i>

7
00:00:22,897 --> 00:00:24,691
<i>Confirm visual. Over.</i>

8
00:00:26,818 --> 00:00:28,945
[soldier] <i>All units,</i>
<i>engage, engage, engage!</i>

9
00:00:29,487 --> 00:00:31,906
- [soldier grunts]
- [Atoy] <i>Two threats down, car secured.</i>

10
00:00:31,990 --> 00:00:33,366
[Atoy] <i>Alpha 1 in pursuit of target.</i>

11
00:00:37,912 --> 00:00:39,247
[Atoy] <i>Raptor to Alpha 1!</i>

12
00:00:39,330 --> 00:00:42,250
<i>Need back up now!</i>
<i>I repeat, need backup now!</i>

13
00:00:43,293 --> 00:00:44,169
[groans]

14
00:00:45,712 --> 00:00:48,006
[Atoy] <i>It's time to unleash</i>
<i>everything you've learned.</i>

15
00:00:48,631 --> 00:00:50,175
<i>Requesting immediate assistance.</i>

16
00:00:50,258 --> 00:00:52,510
<i>I repeat, all members are TIA.</i>

17
00:00:52,594 --> 00:00:53,887
[Domeng] <i>Do you finally</i>
<i>remember who you are,</i>

18
00:00:53,970 --> 00:00:55,221
<i>and where do you live?</i>

19
00:00:55,305 --> 00:00:56,681
[Atoy] <i>I don't remember anything.</i>

20
00:00:57,265 --> 00:01:00,310
[Atoy] <i>I'm finally at Cogon Island,</i>
<i>our identified location.</i>

21
00:01:00,393 --> 00:01:01,519
[Elaine] <i>Who are you, really?</i>

22
00:01:01,603 --> 00:01:04,147
[Atoy] <i>I think</i>
<i>that necklace belongs to me.</i>

23
00:01:04,230 --> 00:01:06,858
But I thought
you didn't remember anything.

24
00:01:06,941 --> 00:01:09,486
[Vilma] <i>That is Saint Anthony of Padua.</i>

25
00:01:09,569 --> 00:01:13,782
<i>He's the patron saint that people pray to</i>
<i>for lost things or missing persons.</i>

26
00:01:13,865 --> 00:01:15,784
[Elaine] <i>I really can't feel</i>
<i>at ease about that person.</i>

27
00:01:15,867 --> 00:01:17,160
<i>There's something off about him.</i>

28
00:01:17,243 --> 00:01:20,413
[Atoy] We need to capture Merelli,
so we can take down Rogue Crescent.

29
00:01:20,497 --> 00:01:23,124
We will suffer serious consequences
if we let them slip.

30
00:01:23,708 --> 00:01:24,542
[Elaine screams]

31
00:01:24,626 --> 00:01:25,585
PREVIOUSLY

32
00:01:29,464 --> 00:01:31,841
[Elaine screaming]

33
00:01:32,801 --> 00:01:35,470
Ouch! [groans]

34
00:01:35,553 --> 00:01:38,139
- [whimpers]
- Why are you following me?

35
00:01:38,223 --> 00:01:40,099
- Ouch! [panting]
- [suave music playing]

36
00:01:40,683 --> 00:01:41,976
[Elaine shouts]

37
00:01:43,311 --> 00:01:44,938
[Elaine whimpers in pain]

38
00:01:45,021 --> 00:01:47,524
You wouldn't have been injured
if it weren't for you stalking me.

39
00:01:47,607 --> 00:01:51,778
You don't have to scold me.
I'm already hurt.

40
00:01:52,445 --> 00:01:55,323
[Elaine sobbing]

41
00:01:55,406 --> 00:01:56,449
[groans]

42
00:01:56,533 --> 00:01:57,659
[Atoy] Come on. Let's go.

43
00:01:57,742 --> 00:01:58,743
[painful exclaim]

44
00:02:00,537 --> 00:02:01,704
[Atoy] Come on.

45
00:02:01,788 --> 00:02:03,665
- Are you injured?
- [groaning in pain]

46
00:02:03,748 --> 00:02:04,874
Hold tight.

47
00:02:05,458 --> 00:02:07,460
[groaning in pain]

48
00:02:07,544 --> 00:02:09,045
[somber music playing]

49
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:11,965
- [Atoy grunts]
- [Elaine whimpers in pain]

50
00:02:13,424 --> 00:02:14,467
[Atoy] Relax.

51
00:02:17,262 --> 00:02:18,263
[soft sobbing]

52
00:02:18,346 --> 00:02:19,681
[Atoy] Oh my…

53
00:02:20,265 --> 00:02:24,018
It's still bleeding.
Your wound needs to be stitched.

54
00:02:24,102 --> 00:02:25,728
What are we going to do?

55
00:02:26,521 --> 00:02:29,149
There's no doctor on the island right now.

56
00:02:30,191 --> 00:02:32,485
The next one will arrive next month.

57
00:02:32,569 --> 00:02:33,570
Leave it to me.

58
00:02:34,487 --> 00:02:36,865
- Come on.
- Wait!

59
00:02:36,948 --> 00:02:37,782
[cheeky music playing]

60
00:02:37,866 --> 00:02:39,284
You're not a doctor.

61
00:02:39,868 --> 00:02:42,078
That wound needs to be stitched
to stop the bleeding,

62
00:02:42,162 --> 00:02:44,747
or you'll die.

63
00:02:44,831 --> 00:02:48,251
You choose. Do I stitch that up,

64
00:02:48,334 --> 00:02:52,213
or do we hold a wake for you
tomorrow or the next day?

65
00:02:52,755 --> 00:02:54,048
[whining]

66
00:02:57,677 --> 00:02:59,137
Fine.

67
00:02:59,220 --> 00:03:00,930
- [Atoy] Okay.
- I won't resist anymore.

68
00:03:01,014 --> 00:03:01,973
[Atoy] All right.

69
00:03:02,557 --> 00:03:05,268
- [Atoy] Remove your bra.
- What?

70
00:03:05,351 --> 00:03:08,521
It's necessary, so I can clean your wound.

71
00:03:10,565 --> 00:03:13,192
[whining]

72
00:03:13,276 --> 00:03:14,694
[Atoy] Come on.

73
00:03:17,113 --> 00:03:18,239
[groans]

74
00:03:19,699 --> 00:03:23,578
- I can't do this. It hurts.
- [Atoy] Just hang in there.

75
00:03:23,661 --> 00:03:26,039
Take it easy. This is no different
from getting a tattoo.

76
00:03:26,122 --> 00:03:27,874
[painful panting]

77
00:03:35,256 --> 00:03:36,925
[shrieking]

78
00:03:37,550 --> 00:03:41,471
[funky music playing]

79
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:49,395
It's not the same thing.

80
00:03:49,479 --> 00:03:51,564
This is worse than getting a tattoo.

81
00:03:51,648 --> 00:03:52,857
[Atoy] It's no different.

82
00:03:53,524 --> 00:03:54,901
It is!

83
00:03:56,027 --> 00:03:57,362
Here, bite it.

84
00:03:58,196 --> 00:03:59,072
Bite it.

85
00:03:59,155 --> 00:04:01,783
Okay? I'll get started now.
Let me stitch this up.

86
00:04:04,577 --> 00:04:05,620
Relax.

87
00:04:07,121 --> 00:04:09,582
[Atoy] Relax. Okay? Relax. Leave it to me.

88
00:04:11,668 --> 00:04:12,502
Okay?

89
00:04:13,336 --> 00:04:15,004
[Atoy] Let's disinfect your wound.

90
00:04:15,588 --> 00:04:17,048
Okay?

91
00:04:17,131 --> 00:04:19,842
[whimpering]

92
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:23,304
[whining]

93
00:04:23,388 --> 00:04:25,974
I am starting now. Relax.

94
00:04:27,642 --> 00:04:29,143
Okay, you're doing good.

95
00:04:32,313 --> 00:04:33,189
[Atoy] Okay…

96
00:04:33,273 --> 00:04:37,485
[funky music continues]

97
00:04:41,739 --> 00:04:44,659
- Bite. Bite harder.
- [moaning]

98
00:04:45,702 --> 00:04:46,619
Okay…

99
00:04:47,912 --> 00:04:49,580
This is just an ant sting.

100
00:04:50,331 --> 00:04:52,417
- A huge ant.
- [groaning]

101
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,502
[groaning]

102
00:04:54,585 --> 00:04:57,588
[funky music continues]

103
00:05:10,476 --> 00:05:11,853
[groaning]

104
00:05:25,533 --> 00:05:27,410
[solemn music playing]

105
00:05:42,258 --> 00:05:44,010
[Doment] Welcome back!

106
00:05:45,970 --> 00:05:48,222
We missed you here, my friend

107
00:05:48,306 --> 00:05:49,849
[Merelli] I don't like
to stay here a long time.

108
00:05:49,932 --> 00:05:51,142
Too hot here now.

109
00:05:51,225 --> 00:05:53,853
[Domeng] Ah! [chuckles]

110
00:05:53,936 --> 00:05:54,771
[curious music playing]

111
00:05:54,854 --> 00:05:56,647
Uh, sir, how was your trip?

112
00:05:58,483 --> 00:06:01,944
Was your trip okay, sir?

113
00:06:03,362 --> 00:06:04,989
Nando, give to Domeng.

114
00:06:14,415 --> 00:06:15,416
Oh…

115
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:18,252
Oh, thank you very much, my friend.

116
00:06:18,336 --> 00:06:20,088
By the way, uh… Oh…

117
00:06:22,340 --> 00:06:25,259
Do you have, uh,
a gift for us from Italia?

118
00:06:25,885 --> 00:06:28,054
- Of course.
- Hi, darling!

119
00:06:28,137 --> 00:06:29,222
[Merelli in Italian] My sweetheart.

120
00:06:30,890 --> 00:06:32,058
[giggles]

121
00:06:34,894 --> 00:06:36,395
I missed you.

122
00:06:36,479 --> 00:06:37,480
[girl chuckles softly]

123
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:44,946
[music concludes]

124
00:06:53,371 --> 00:06:55,998
[Elaine groans, whinces]

125
00:06:57,708 --> 00:06:58,835
‪[sharp exhale]

126
00:07:01,587 --> 00:07:04,132
I'm going to put medicine
on your wound, okay?

127
00:07:07,468 --> 00:07:08,678
[whinces]

128
00:07:11,222 --> 00:07:12,223
Relax.

129
00:07:12,723 --> 00:07:15,476
If I wanted to take advantage of you,
I would've done it earlier.

130
00:07:22,483 --> 00:07:26,154
[breathing sharply]

131
00:07:26,237 --> 00:07:27,447
[Atoy] Shh…

132
00:07:28,865 --> 00:07:29,699
‪[sharp exhale]

133
00:07:32,452 --> 00:07:34,745
What were you doing
at the cove earlier, anyway?

134
00:07:34,829 --> 00:07:37,206
[sinister music playing]

135
00:07:37,290 --> 00:07:38,791
I followed you

136
00:07:39,792 --> 00:07:42,503
to return your necklace.

137
00:07:42,587 --> 00:07:44,714
I know it's yours anyway.

138
00:07:45,882 --> 00:07:48,134
Why didn't you just
give it back yesterday?

139
00:07:49,343 --> 00:07:50,970
Just didn't feel like it.

140
00:07:51,053 --> 00:07:52,555
What were you doing there?

141
00:07:53,139 --> 00:07:56,809
And how did you know I was around?

142
00:07:57,727 --> 00:07:59,228
I've got a keen sense of smell.

143
00:07:59,312 --> 00:08:02,773
And you climbed so fast.

144
00:08:03,357 --> 00:08:05,610
You're faster than the locals.

145
00:08:07,069 --> 00:08:08,696
Are you a mountaineer?

146
00:08:09,447 --> 00:08:12,450
And where did you find that medical kit?

147
00:08:12,992 --> 00:08:15,578
And why do you know how to stitch a wound?

148
00:08:17,955 --> 00:08:19,415
I bet you're a doctor.

149
00:08:20,666 --> 00:08:22,668
A doctor who's also a mountaineer.

150
00:08:24,378 --> 00:08:26,422
See? That's what I'm saying.

151
00:08:27,006 --> 00:08:29,342
There's something you're not telling us.

152
00:08:29,926 --> 00:08:32,178
Honestly, do you even have amnesia?

153
00:08:32,929 --> 00:08:37,808
You know, Miss Elaine, you need to rest.

154
00:08:38,351 --> 00:08:39,977
It's the only way your wound will heal.

155
00:08:40,645 --> 00:08:43,231
Come on, I'll take you
so you can finally get cleaned up.

156
00:08:43,314 --> 00:08:45,775
[mid-tempo curious music]

157
00:08:45,858 --> 00:08:48,194
Ah… [clears throat] Over here.

158
00:08:50,446 --> 00:08:54,283
[Elaine groaning]

159
00:08:57,537 --> 00:08:59,455
[suave music playing]

160
00:08:59,539 --> 00:09:01,207
FATHER'S LANE
FOOD HUB IN BACLARAN

161
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:39,370
[electronic bleeping]

162
00:09:46,085 --> 00:09:48,629
[grunting]

163
00:09:50,423 --> 00:09:51,549
Thank you.

164
00:09:52,842 --> 00:09:54,343
[inaudible]

165
00:09:55,761 --> 00:09:56,637
‪[grunts]

166
00:10:03,102 --> 00:10:03,936
Uh…

167
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:06,230
The wound might open up.

168
00:10:06,314 --> 00:10:08,316
It could bleed more. If you want…

169
00:10:08,399 --> 00:10:10,401
Do you want me
to help you, if that's okay?

170
00:10:11,068 --> 00:10:13,738
No, no. I'm fine.
I can handle it on my own.

171
00:10:16,490 --> 00:10:17,658
All right.

172
00:10:19,660 --> 00:10:20,661
[Atoy] Uh…

173
00:10:22,663 --> 00:10:27,543
[cheeky music playing]

174
00:10:31,839 --> 00:10:34,050
[groaning] Ouch.

175
00:10:34,133 --> 00:10:36,510
Are you all right?
That might take you forever.

176
00:10:36,594 --> 00:10:38,179
My goodness, you're not helping!

177
00:10:38,262 --> 00:10:39,680
You're the one who refused my help.

178
00:10:40,681 --> 00:10:42,308
[shrieks]

179
00:10:42,391 --> 00:10:44,727
[groans, panting]

180
00:10:44,810 --> 00:10:46,979
- Did you see something?
- [Atoy] No, no!

181
00:10:47,063 --> 00:10:48,939
I didn't see anything!
Nothing! I didn't see anything!

182
00:10:49,023 --> 00:10:50,024
Just the papaya.

183
00:10:50,107 --> 00:10:51,150
The papaya?! [panting]

184
00:10:53,152 --> 00:10:54,737
Yes, the papaya on the calendar.

185
00:10:57,073 --> 00:11:00,785
[breathing heavily]

186
00:11:09,001 --> 00:11:09,835
‪[music concludes]

187
00:11:15,508 --> 00:11:18,552
- Why are you taking so long?
- This is tough.

188
00:11:19,512 --> 00:11:21,972
Sorry if I can't help you.
I know nothing about bras.

189
00:11:23,599 --> 00:11:24,517
There we go.

190
00:11:26,352 --> 00:11:27,311
Ah…

191
00:11:30,398 --> 00:11:34,443
Please grab my clothes from the cabinet.

192
00:11:35,069 --> 00:11:36,195
Please.

193
00:11:45,287 --> 00:11:47,164
- This?
- Yes.

194
00:11:50,167 --> 00:11:54,672
[gentle music playing]

195
00:12:01,303 --> 00:12:02,388
[Atoy sighs]

196
00:12:03,472 --> 00:12:04,515
Ah…

197
00:12:05,683 --> 00:12:08,185
- You want me to help you?
- Yes.

198
00:12:12,731 --> 00:12:16,819
[gentle music continues]

199
00:12:29,123 --> 00:12:30,791
- Slowly.
- [sighs]

200
00:12:32,126 --> 00:12:33,210
Okay, there we go.

201
00:13:06,577 --> 00:13:09,455
I'll put the skirt on.

202
00:13:09,538 --> 00:13:10,956
Your skirt? Hold on.

203
00:13:14,335 --> 00:13:15,461
[Atoy clears throat]

204
00:13:22,676 --> 00:13:24,595
Your picture here is beautiful.

205
00:13:25,596 --> 00:13:26,805
Is this your mom?

206
00:13:26,889 --> 00:13:29,975
Yes, but she's no longer around.

207
00:13:30,059 --> 00:13:31,268
[Atoy] Mmm.

208
00:13:31,977 --> 00:13:37,483
You said you still have
a few memories of your mom.

209
00:13:39,026 --> 00:13:40,486
Ah, yes.

210
00:13:42,696 --> 00:13:44,240
She was a teacher too, just like you.

211
00:13:44,323 --> 00:13:47,785
I remembered her because of that necklace.

212
00:13:49,036 --> 00:13:50,538
She gave it to me.

213
00:13:59,380 --> 00:14:00,256
Here.

214
00:14:01,006 --> 00:14:04,927
Sorry for not…
returning it to you right away.

215
00:14:06,512 --> 00:14:08,931
- Thank you.
- Thanks for your help.

216
00:14:16,564 --> 00:14:18,107
You can go now.

217
00:14:18,190 --> 00:14:21,861
Do you need my help? Just let me know.

218
00:14:21,944 --> 00:14:24,238
I can actually stay here to help you.

219
00:14:24,321 --> 00:14:25,406
I'm fine.

220
00:14:25,489 --> 00:14:27,533
I can manage.

221
00:14:27,616 --> 00:14:30,661
- You sure?
- Yes, you can go back to your place now.

222
00:14:30,744 --> 00:14:31,745
All right, then.

223
00:14:38,168 --> 00:14:40,754
[uneasy music playing]

224
00:14:50,681 --> 00:14:52,391
Aren't you going to leave?

225
00:14:52,474 --> 00:14:53,642
- Hey…
- [Elaine] I bet you're a thief.

226
00:14:54,184 --> 00:14:55,603
- Or you could be a rapist.
- Hey…

227
00:14:56,437 --> 00:14:59,315
A thief? A rapist, really now?
I helped you, remember?

228
00:14:59,398 --> 00:15:01,775
How do I know
you're not just pretending to be kind

229
00:15:01,859 --> 00:15:03,485
to gain my trust.

230
00:15:03,569 --> 00:15:06,363
And after that, you might steal
from me, or worse, rape me!

231
00:15:06,447 --> 00:15:09,074
- Are you for real? Really now?
- [panicked breathing]

232
00:15:09,158 --> 00:15:10,075
[shrieks]

233
00:15:10,701 --> 00:15:12,077
Stop denying it!

234
00:15:12,578 --> 00:15:13,954
Who are you really, huh?

235
00:15:14,038 --> 00:15:16,081
I know your amnesia isn't real!

236
00:15:16,665 --> 00:15:18,250
What are you really doing here?

237
00:15:18,334 --> 00:15:21,128
- Why? Am I the only one pretending?
- [heavy breathing]

238
00:15:21,211 --> 00:15:22,463
Look at your stuff.

239
00:15:22,546 --> 00:15:25,382
No daycare teacher on this island
has anything like that.

240
00:15:25,466 --> 00:15:27,092
You're from Manila, aren't you?

241
00:15:27,176 --> 00:15:30,304
And those pictures of yours…
Your picture with your mom…

242
00:15:30,971 --> 00:15:32,723
- This was taken in Europe.
- [gasps]

243
00:15:32,806 --> 00:15:35,225
- You're not just capable, you're rich.
- [heavy breathing]

244
00:15:35,809 --> 00:15:37,144
Who are you really?

245
00:15:37,728 --> 00:15:39,980
Why are you prolonging
your stay on this island?

246
00:15:40,064 --> 00:15:41,815
That's none of your business!

247
00:15:41,899 --> 00:15:44,151
You're the one I keep asking,

248
00:15:44,860 --> 00:15:46,904
and yet, you can't answer
a single question?

249
00:15:46,987 --> 00:15:48,405
We're just the same.

250
00:15:49,490 --> 00:15:50,324
L-Let go of me!

251
00:15:50,407 --> 00:15:52,451
[grunts and yelps]

252
00:15:52,534 --> 00:15:54,954
[panting]

253
00:16:07,841 --> 00:16:08,676
‪[gasps]

254
00:16:09,218 --> 00:16:10,970
[dreamy music playing]

255
00:16:17,142 --> 00:16:18,018
You pervert!

256
00:16:18,102 --> 00:16:20,312
[shrieking]

257
00:16:20,396 --> 00:16:21,230
‪-[panicked breathing]
‪-[unsettling music]

258
00:16:22,189 --> 00:16:24,900
Get out of here! Out!

259
00:16:24,984 --> 00:16:26,110
You pervert!

260
00:16:26,193 --> 00:16:28,404
[panting]

261
00:16:29,989 --> 00:16:31,824
[panting]

262
00:16:42,001 --> 00:16:45,295
♪ <i>Sweetheart</i> ♪

263
00:16:45,379 --> 00:16:49,174
- [children cheering and applauding]
- [indistinct]

264
00:16:49,258 --> 00:16:51,343
Here you go!

265
00:16:51,427 --> 00:16:54,221
Since today is the last day of school,

266
00:16:54,304 --> 00:16:56,098
everyone gets a free meal!

267
00:16:56,181 --> 00:16:58,517
[cheering and applauding]

268
00:16:58,600 --> 00:17:01,437
[sentimental music playing]

269
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:03,147
[screams]

270
00:17:03,230 --> 00:17:04,231
[groans]

271
00:17:09,111 --> 00:17:11,780
Elaine, you've been spacing out
for a while. Are you okay?

272
00:17:14,324 --> 00:17:15,993
Yes, I'm fine.

273
00:17:16,076 --> 00:17:18,245
Oh, you're not wearing
your necklace anymore.

274
00:17:18,328 --> 00:17:20,581
Did you finally return it to Mr. Amnesia?

275
00:17:24,918 --> 00:17:28,047
Tell me what happened next.
Come on, tell me.

276
00:17:28,130 --> 00:17:29,381
Did you guys talk?

277
00:17:30,841 --> 00:17:34,261
- No, I left right away.
- Ah.

278
00:17:38,432 --> 00:17:40,601
[suave music playing]

279
00:17:41,185 --> 00:17:42,436
[Elaine] Ah…

280
00:17:42,519 --> 00:17:43,604
Ah…

281
00:17:43,687 --> 00:17:45,355
What do you want?

282
00:17:45,939 --> 00:17:47,983
How are you doing? Did you get a fever?

283
00:17:49,109 --> 00:17:50,736
I'm sorry about last night.

284
00:17:50,819 --> 00:17:54,323
You two were together last night, I see.

285
00:17:54,406 --> 00:17:55,616
But you didn't talk to each other?

286
00:17:57,034 --> 00:17:59,078
The clothes you left last night,

287
00:17:59,161 --> 00:18:01,205
I put them by your door.

288
00:18:01,288 --> 00:18:04,166
And I also bought this for you.

289
00:18:04,249 --> 00:18:06,710
And… I hope it fits.

290
00:18:06,794 --> 00:18:09,338
My bad, I accidentally damaged it.

291
00:18:09,421 --> 00:18:13,300
You two didn't talk, yet you managed
to leave behind some clothes.

292
00:18:13,926 --> 00:18:17,012
Hmm… I know exactly where this is going.

293
00:18:17,096 --> 00:18:18,555
[quirky music]

294
00:18:18,639 --> 00:18:20,224
Just leave already.

295
00:18:20,307 --> 00:18:21,725
OMG.

296
00:18:21,809 --> 00:18:23,143
He broke.

297
00:18:24,019 --> 00:18:26,522
- Teacher, you dropped your bra!
- [funky music playing]

298
00:18:26,605 --> 00:18:29,900
That's not a bra! That's actually Monay.

299
00:18:30,484 --> 00:18:31,318
[gasps]

300
00:18:33,278 --> 00:18:35,572
No, it's a bra! Just like my sister's!

301
00:18:40,327 --> 00:18:41,829
[huffs]

302
00:18:42,412 --> 00:18:46,166
[funky music continues]

303
00:19:19,241 --> 00:19:20,576
He knows how to sew.

304
00:19:22,411 --> 00:19:25,956
[gentle music playing]

305
00:19:27,541 --> 00:19:28,542
[Atoy] Elaine…

306
00:19:31,086 --> 00:19:32,004
[gasps]

307
00:19:32,087 --> 00:19:33,922
Why are you coming
to my house unannounced?

308
00:19:34,006 --> 00:19:34,840
Can we talk?

309
00:19:34,923 --> 00:19:36,008
Go out!

310
00:19:37,009 --> 00:19:39,469
Hold on… [stammers]
What? Are you mad at me?

311
00:19:39,553 --> 00:19:41,054
Shouldn't you be grateful instead?

312
00:19:42,139 --> 00:19:46,226
Thanks, but you still piss me off. [huffs]

313
00:19:46,310 --> 00:19:48,687
You really want to make it look like
something happened between us last night?

314
00:19:49,688 --> 00:19:50,898
[scoffs]

315
00:19:52,691 --> 00:19:55,611
I can't help it
if they're all green-minded.

316
00:19:55,694 --> 00:19:57,237
There's not much I can do about it.

317
00:19:57,321 --> 00:19:59,489
But you still humiliated me.

318
00:19:59,573 --> 00:20:01,950
I never asked you to buy me a bra.

319
00:20:02,034 --> 00:20:05,412
We're not that close.
We don't even know each other.

320
00:20:05,495 --> 00:20:09,458
I don't even know your name,
yet you just kissed me out of nowhere.

321
00:20:10,083 --> 00:20:11,418
Drop the act. I know you liked it.

322
00:20:12,294 --> 00:20:14,046
You shameless fool!

323
00:20:14,129 --> 00:20:16,131
You were the one who came close to me.

324
00:20:16,715 --> 00:20:18,759
- You didn't even try to avoid me.
- [gasps]

325
00:20:18,842 --> 00:20:20,886
Because I was terrified!

326
00:20:21,595 --> 00:20:23,305
For all we know, you could have killed me.

327
00:20:23,388 --> 00:20:24,431
Oh…

328
00:20:25,057 --> 00:20:26,767
If I were a bad person,

329
00:20:27,434 --> 00:20:29,728
why did you let me treat your wound?

330
00:20:31,104 --> 00:20:32,940
Why did you follow me then?

331
00:20:35,400 --> 00:20:36,568
I don't know.

332
00:20:39,238 --> 00:20:40,364
You know.

333
00:20:42,115 --> 00:20:43,158
You know,

334
00:20:43,909 --> 00:20:45,410
but you just don't want to admit it.

335
00:20:46,620 --> 00:20:47,746
Hmm?

336
00:20:57,923 --> 00:20:59,383
Just say the word.

337
00:21:02,094 --> 00:21:03,136
Then I will just go.

338
00:21:26,034 --> 00:21:28,620
[feel-good music]

339
00:21:33,208 --> 00:21:34,710
Your hair is so soft, Mark.

340
00:21:35,419 --> 00:21:38,588
- Who's Mark?
- Maybe that's your name.

341
00:21:40,632 --> 00:21:42,009
If not Mark…

342
00:21:43,176 --> 00:21:44,011
Ryan?

343
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:45,762
Wait, wait.

344
00:21:46,763 --> 00:21:49,766
You also look like… a Joshua.

345
00:21:49,850 --> 00:21:53,061
- Ah, wait. From this angle…
- Joshua…

346
00:21:54,229 --> 00:21:55,105
Enzo?

347
00:21:56,189 --> 00:21:58,567
- Enzo.
- [chuckles] Enzo…

348
00:21:58,650 --> 00:22:01,903
The names you've mentioned
sound like rich men names.

349
00:22:01,987 --> 00:22:04,239
Oh, all right, all right. Hmm…

350
00:22:04,323 --> 00:22:05,615
Godofredo.

351
00:22:06,199 --> 00:22:07,200
- You want?
- Godofredo?

352
00:22:07,284 --> 00:22:08,744
Restituto?

353
00:22:09,703 --> 00:22:10,954
Oh, I know now!

354
00:22:11,038 --> 00:22:13,290
- Okay, I got it now!
- Tell me.

355
00:22:13,373 --> 00:22:14,750
Dominador!

356
00:22:14,833 --> 00:22:17,419
- That sounds like an old person's name!
- [chuckles]

357
00:22:17,502 --> 00:22:18,879
[whimsical music playing]

358
00:22:18,962 --> 00:22:20,339
This might surprise you, but…

359
00:22:22,090 --> 00:22:23,759
you look like a…

360
00:22:25,093 --> 00:22:26,136
Napoy…

361
00:22:27,345 --> 00:22:29,264
Or maybe… Atoy.

362
00:22:29,347 --> 00:22:30,974
- Ah…
- Or Dodong.

363
00:22:31,058 --> 00:22:32,768
You look like someone
who'd have those names.

364
00:22:32,851 --> 00:22:37,314
[bright feel-good music]

365
00:22:47,699 --> 00:22:49,743
That's a lot of catch! [chuckles]

366
00:22:49,826 --> 00:22:50,827
How are you doing?

367
00:23:00,253 --> 00:23:04,132
[sinister rock music playing]

368
00:23:15,185 --> 00:23:17,729
[Atoy] Our main target is Abel Merelli,

369
00:23:17,813 --> 00:23:20,941
an Italian Argentinian
businessman and billionaire

370
00:23:21,024 --> 00:23:23,401
and is the main funder
of the paramilitary group.

371
00:23:30,492 --> 00:23:31,368
Sir.

372
00:23:32,035 --> 00:23:34,871
Has any boat with foreigners
on it arrived here?

373
00:23:34,955 --> 00:23:36,248
You can ask the village chief.

374
00:23:36,331 --> 00:23:40,127
They should know
if any tourists have already docked.

375
00:23:41,503 --> 00:23:42,587
The village chief?

376
00:23:47,092 --> 00:23:48,802
[Ponyo] Sir, this is yours!

377
00:23:49,803 --> 00:23:51,346
We saved some for you.

378
00:23:57,018 --> 00:23:58,145
Who gave this to you?

379
00:23:58,854 --> 00:24:01,565
The foreigner you mentioned
who lives in the white house?

380
00:24:01,648 --> 00:24:04,234
No, it was Sir Domeng who gave it.

381
00:24:04,317 --> 00:24:06,444
He even hands them out at his office.

382
00:24:06,528 --> 00:24:08,405
You can still ask for one, sir.

383
00:24:10,115 --> 00:24:14,452
[rock music continues]

384
00:24:26,673 --> 00:24:29,509
[Domeng stammers] Don't touch that.

385
00:24:29,593 --> 00:24:30,594
It's not yours, okay?

386
00:24:30,677 --> 00:24:32,846
It's expensive. It's imported.

387
00:24:33,847 --> 00:24:35,182
[man] Did you come from another country?

388
00:24:35,265 --> 00:24:38,310
[Domeng] No.
A friend of mine gave it to me.

389
00:24:38,393 --> 00:24:40,562
That souvenir comes in two boxes.

390
00:24:41,521 --> 00:24:43,148
That person is filthy rich.

391
00:24:46,401 --> 00:24:50,739
Ah, so later, make sure
to send off the pumpboats, okay?

392
00:24:50,822 --> 00:24:53,867
He'll be leaving at seven.
His yacht his arriving soon.

393
00:24:53,950 --> 00:24:55,619
- [man 1] Ah, really?
- [man 2] All right, then.

394
00:24:55,702 --> 00:24:57,162
[Domeng] He's going to have
a hard time for sure.

395
00:24:57,245 --> 00:24:58,538
- [man 1] Of course!
- [Domeng] Otherwise,

396
00:24:58,622 --> 00:24:59,956
we wouldn't have any souvenirs.

397
00:25:00,040 --> 00:25:02,042
- [Domeng] Think about it.
- [man 1] We'll make him leave later.

398
00:25:02,125 --> 00:25:02,959
- [Domeng] Got it!
- [man 1] Yes.

399
00:25:03,043 --> 00:25:03,877
[man 1] Can we enjoy ourselves now?

400
00:25:03,960 --> 00:25:05,754
I'll deal with that later.

401
00:25:05,837 --> 00:25:08,381
[inquisitive music playing]

402
00:25:19,851 --> 00:25:21,353
[knock on the door]

403
00:25:26,399 --> 00:25:27,359
[sighs]

404
00:25:27,442 --> 00:25:28,443
Uh… Vilma…

405
00:25:29,319 --> 00:25:30,362
What brings you here?

406
00:25:30,445 --> 00:25:32,948
I saw Mr. Amnesia.

407
00:25:33,031 --> 00:25:35,075
He was eavesdropping
on the guards' conversation earlier.

408
00:25:36,034 --> 00:25:37,702
I think your suspicions
about him were right.

409
00:25:38,286 --> 00:25:40,789
His behavior earlier was suspicious.

410
00:25:41,581 --> 00:25:42,999
He might have another agenda.

411
00:25:43,792 --> 00:25:46,753
Did you see where he went?

412
00:25:46,836 --> 00:25:48,046
No.

413
00:25:49,673 --> 00:25:50,715
[Vilma sighs]

414
00:25:52,050 --> 00:25:54,970
Sir. The target has arrived.

415
00:25:55,053 --> 00:25:58,890
I repeat, I am confirming
that the target has arrived.

416
00:25:58,974 --> 00:26:00,350
He arrived last night

417
00:26:00,433 --> 00:26:02,477
and will be leaving later, at 1900 hours.

418
00:26:02,560 --> 00:26:03,979
- Do you copy?
- [Mercado on radio] <i>Copy.</i>

419
00:26:04,062 --> 00:26:05,522
<i>FS Karayom deployed.</i>

420
00:26:05,605 --> 00:26:10,610
<i>Strike team staging at city port.</i>
<i>Logistics on fast boat.</i>

421
00:26:10,694 --> 00:26:11,778
Let's move.

422
00:26:11,861 --> 00:26:16,408
[tense music continues]

423
00:26:27,752 --> 00:26:28,753
[Elaine shrieks]

424
00:26:30,213 --> 00:26:31,965
‪[exhilarating tense music]

425
00:26:37,262 --> 00:26:38,847
You shouldn't have followed me here.

426
00:26:38,930 --> 00:26:40,348
Is this what you're hiding from me?

427
00:26:43,059 --> 00:26:45,562
What is this for?

428
00:26:46,563 --> 00:26:48,023
Who are you, really?

429
00:26:48,106 --> 00:26:48,940
‪[somber music]

430
00:26:51,109 --> 00:26:52,152
Elaine…

431
00:26:52,736 --> 00:26:54,988
Elaine, I can explain.

432
00:26:55,071 --> 00:26:57,407
Please, let me explain.

433
00:26:58,950 --> 00:27:00,660
I don't want to hear it from you!

434
00:27:02,454 --> 00:27:05,749
Did my father send you here? Is that it?

435
00:27:08,501 --> 00:27:10,128
I have no idea
what you're talking about, Elaine.

436
00:27:10,211 --> 00:27:12,589
I'm harmless. Elaine, there's no…

437
00:27:12,672 --> 00:27:15,425
There's no reason for you to be scared.
Elaine, trust me.

438
00:27:15,508 --> 00:27:17,761
I really want to trust you.

439
00:27:18,261 --> 00:27:20,263
I was actually starting to fall for it.

440
00:27:21,723 --> 00:27:26,353
Until I finally realized
how great you are at pretending.

441
00:27:29,606 --> 00:27:31,316
Who are you, really?

442
00:27:32,108 --> 00:27:33,151
Elaine.

443
00:27:34,694 --> 00:27:36,988
You have to trust me, please.

444
00:27:38,365 --> 00:27:39,240
Please.

445
00:27:44,037 --> 00:27:45,955
- Please.
- How?

446
00:27:48,750 --> 00:27:52,420
How do you expect me
to trust a complete stranger?

447
00:28:05,683 --> 00:28:06,559
Take it.

448
00:28:11,147 --> 00:28:12,607
This holds so much value to me.

449
00:28:12,690 --> 00:28:15,944
[hopeful music playing]

450
00:28:18,905 --> 00:28:21,533
I'll be back for it. I'll be back for you.

451
00:28:21,616 --> 00:28:22,742
Later tonight,

452
00:28:24,577 --> 00:28:26,246
I'll tell you everything you need to know.

453
00:28:50,270 --> 00:28:52,230
[gentle music]

454
00:28:52,313 --> 00:28:53,148
[Atoy] Sir.

455
00:28:54,357 --> 00:28:56,359
- Good day.
- Good day to you too.

456
00:28:56,943 --> 00:28:57,777
Who owns that?

457
00:28:58,361 --> 00:29:01,072
Oh, that? It belongs
to Sir Domeng's visitor.

458
00:29:01,906 --> 00:29:05,702
One guy said
he was supposed to arrive tonight.

459
00:29:05,785 --> 00:29:07,620
But he got here early instead.

460
00:29:08,621 --> 00:29:10,290
Because of an emergency.

461
00:29:11,374 --> 00:29:14,502
I could no longer
bring this to the town proper.

462
00:29:14,586 --> 00:29:16,546
I hope they hurry up and leave.

463
00:29:18,798 --> 00:29:20,300
I see. Thank you.

464
00:29:20,383 --> 00:29:23,386
[brazen music playing]

465
00:29:29,142 --> 00:29:31,603
Sir, Sir, target is moving
ahead of schedule.

466
00:29:31,686 --> 00:29:34,189
I advise you instruct
the strike team to move now,

467
00:29:34,272 --> 00:29:35,398
move now to the main port.

468
00:29:35,482 --> 00:29:36,983
[Mercado on phone]
<i>Maintain intercept posture.</i>

469
00:29:37,066 --> 00:29:38,943
<i>Improvise if you have to.</i>

470
00:29:39,027 --> 00:29:40,528
<i>Target must be captured.</i>

471
00:29:40,612 --> 00:29:41,613
Copy.

472
00:29:41,696 --> 00:29:45,909
[inquisitive music playing]

473
00:29:45,992 --> 00:29:46,993
Sir.

474
00:29:49,496 --> 00:29:50,497
How much for this?

475
00:29:51,289 --> 00:29:55,168
[brazen music playing]

476
00:30:02,467 --> 00:30:03,676
[Atoy] Sir!

477
00:30:05,136 --> 00:30:07,722
Sir. You want some crabs?

478
00:30:07,806 --> 00:30:09,516
Very, very good crabs.

479
00:30:09,599 --> 00:30:12,352
Um, very, very fat! You want?

480
00:30:14,187 --> 00:30:17,357
[tense music playing]

481
00:30:21,486 --> 00:30:23,822
You don't look like
you selling crabs, mister.

482
00:30:25,323 --> 00:30:27,075
[upbeat tense music playing]

483
00:30:43,591 --> 00:30:45,510
Help!

484
00:30:45,593 --> 00:30:46,678
[man] Drop the gun!

485
00:30:46,761 --> 00:30:48,638
- Or else, I'll end his life!
- Help me! Please, don't!

486
00:30:50,098 --> 00:30:50,932
[man] Drop it!

487
00:30:51,015 --> 00:30:52,684
Help me!

488
00:30:53,726 --> 00:30:56,062
[suspenseful music playing]

489
00:30:59,232 --> 00:31:01,025
- [man] I'm starting to get impatient!
- [Ponyo shouting]

490
00:31:01,109 --> 00:31:02,610
- Drop it!
- [Ponyo crying]

491
00:31:02,694 --> 00:31:03,611
Okay, okay, okay!

492
00:31:03,695 --> 00:31:04,863
[Ponyo sobbing]

493
00:31:04,946 --> 00:31:07,031
Drop the gun! Get rid of it!

494
00:31:08,074 --> 00:31:10,410
- Drop it!
- [Ponyo sobbing] Help me!

495
00:31:10,952 --> 00:31:13,496
- [uneasy music playing]
- [gun thuds]

496
00:31:16,624 --> 00:31:18,668
Kill that boy… Now!

497
00:31:18,751 --> 00:31:19,794
[Ponyo screaming]

498
00:31:19,878 --> 00:31:20,712
‪[energetic action music]

499
00:31:44,027 --> 00:31:45,778
[men screaming]

500
00:31:47,030 --> 00:31:49,115
Kill him! Bastard!

501
00:31:53,036 --> 00:31:55,204
[Merelli speaks in Italian and English]
Kill that man!

502
00:31:55,288 --> 00:31:58,666
[Merelli speaks in Italian and English]
Take that kid!

503
00:31:58,750 --> 00:32:01,169
[Merelli] Go! Faster!

504
00:32:01,252 --> 00:32:02,378
[Merelli] Come now!

505
00:32:02,462 --> 00:32:03,296
‪[Ponyo crying, shouting]

506
00:32:06,633 --> 00:32:09,385
[Ponyo screams] Help! Help!

507
00:32:17,393 --> 00:32:19,812
[dramatic action music]

508
00:32:20,855 --> 00:32:23,566
- [thudding]
- [grunting]

509
00:32:31,616 --> 00:32:33,201
[grunting and groaning]

510
00:32:37,622 --> 00:32:38,456
[goon screams]

511
00:32:41,626 --> 00:32:43,336
[grunting]

512
00:32:55,223 --> 00:32:56,766
[Ponyo] Sir!

513
00:32:56,849 --> 00:32:59,936
[brazen music playing]

514
00:33:23,668 --> 00:33:26,796
[intense music playing]

515
00:33:33,761 --> 00:33:34,846
You really changed a lot

516
00:33:34,929 --> 00:33:37,765
because of your stubborn
rebellion against me!

517
00:33:37,849 --> 00:33:40,101
It's your fault that I distanced myself!

518
00:33:40,184 --> 00:33:41,561
[sinister music]

519
00:33:41,644 --> 00:33:44,814
Maybe you want us to dig up
what just you did.

520
00:33:44,897 --> 00:33:46,566
Her vitals are doing well now.

521
00:33:46,649 --> 00:33:48,568
Audrey will not wake up tonight.

522
00:33:48,651 --> 00:33:49,527
You'll never know.

523
00:33:49,610 --> 00:33:54,240
I want to be the first person
my prodigal daughter sees.

524
00:33:54,323 --> 00:33:57,201
Atoy, bring back
the missing San Antonio De Padua.

525
00:33:57,285 --> 00:33:58,745
You've been out for a long time.

526
00:33:58,828 --> 00:34:01,122
[man] <i>Who knows you are the thief.</i>

527
